---
import LegalPage from "../../components/LegalPage.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../../config";
---

<LegalPage
  lang="en"
  title="Privacy — ai-mods"
  description="Privacy policy for ai-mods: hosting, cookies, tracking and your rights."
  alternatePath="/datenschutz/"
>
  <h1>Privacy</h1>

  <p class="note">
    Courtesy translation of the German <a href="/datenschutz/"
      >Datenschutzerklärung</a
    >, which is the legally binding version.
  </p>

  <h2>Controller</h2>
  <address>
    Christian Perkuhn<br />
    ai-mods<br />
    Matterstockstraße 5<br />
    97080 Würzburg<br />
    Germany<br />
    Email: <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}>{siteConfig.email}</a>
  </address>

  <h2>Hosting</h2>
  <p>
    This website is hosted by STRATO AG, Otto-Ostrowski-Straße 7, 10249 Berlin,
    Germany. When the pages are requested, the host processes technically
    necessary server log data: IP address, time of access, requested file and
    the transmitted browser identifier (user agent).
  </p>
  <p>
    The purpose of this processing is the technical operation, stability and
    security of the website. The legal basis is Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR (legitimate
    interest in a secure and functional service). A data processing agreement
    under Art. 28 GDPR is in place with the host. The log data is deleted by the
    host according to its retention periods.
  </p>

  <h2>No cookies, no tracking</h2>
  <p>
    This website sets no cookies and embeds no analytics or tracking services.
    There is no audience measurement and no profiling. Beyond the technical
    operation handled by the host, no data is transferred to third parties.
  </p>

  <h2>Self-hosted fonts</h2>
  <p>
    All fonts are served locally from this server. There is no connection to
    Google Fonts or other third-party servers, and no data is transferred to
    third parties in the process.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact by email</h2>
  <p>
    If you contact me by email, I process the details you send solely to handle
    your request. The legal basis is Art. 6 (1) (b) GDPR where the request
    concerns the initiation of a contract, otherwise Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR. The
    data is deleted once it is no longer required and no statutory retention
    obligations prevent this.
  </p>

  <h2>External links</h2>
  <p>
    This website links to external services (GitHub, LinkedIn, Steam). When you
    follow these links, the privacy policies of the respective providers apply,
    over whose processing I have no influence.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    You have the right to access (Art. 15 GDPR), rectification (Art. 16),
    erasure (Art. 17), restriction of processing (Art. 18), data portability
    (Art. 20) and objection (Art. 21). You also have the right to lodge a
    complaint with a supervisory authority. The competent authority is the
    Bavarian State Office for Data Protection Supervision (BayLDA), Ansbach.
  </p>

  <p>Last updated: July 2026</p>
</LegalPage>
